      "content": "I understand your frustration with your current treatment, but warfarin is a carefully calibrated medication that requires regular monitoring to ensure it's working correctly and safely. Garlic extract and vitamin K can have unpredictable effects on blood clotting and may not provide the stable and consistent anticoagulation that warfarin offers. It's crucial to follow your doctor's advice and not try to replace your medication with unproven methods. The risks of self-medicating with these substances could lead to serious complications, including life-threatening bleeding or clotting events. Always consult with your healthcare provider before making any changes to your treatment plan.",
